_meta.title: CA Electrification Programs
_meta.description: California residential electrification rebate and incentive programs. 107 programs covering federal, state, regional, CCA, municipal utility, AQMD grant, and financing programs.
notes: Program codes R4.1 (programs 27+33) and R5.1 (programs 28+34) have duplicates — resolve before DB insert
Program 52 SGIP HPWH: valid_until 2026-01-01 but is_active true — verify current status
Programs 55, 72, 73, 74: available_zip_codes uses county names, not ZIP arrays — needs enrichment
Federal §25C (program 24) is is_active:false — expired 2025-12-31, kept for 2025 tax filing reference
SLO APCD Woodsmoke (program 98) is is_active:false — out of funds, waitlist only as of Feb 2026

programs.program_name: Inflation Reduction Act - HEEHRA Point-of-Sale Rebates
programs.description: Federal IRA-funded point-of-sale rebates for LMI households switching from gas to high-efficiency electric appliances.
programs.application_process: 1. Income verify at portal. 2. Get voucher. 3. Contractor deducts from invoice.

programs.description: State-funded adders for LMI households to cover the gap between standard rebates and full electrification costs.
programs.application_process: Contractor submits claim through TECH portal post-install.

programs.description: Provides nearly 100% cost coverage for battery storage systems for vulnerable or LMI customers.
programs.application_process: Developer/Contractor submits RRF reservation before install.

programs.description: Instant coupons for high-efficiency water heaters and thermostats at major retailers.
programs.application_process: Generate coupon code on website and present at checkout (online or in-store).
cannot_stack_with: TECH (Contractor cannot claim if consumer used coupon)

programs.description: State-administered financing for residential energy projects with 0% rate options for LMI customers.
programs.application_process: 1. Choose contractor. 2. Apply with credit union. 3. Project funding paid to contractor.

programs.description: High-value rebates for City of Los Angeles residents converting gas appliances to all-electric systems.
programs.application_process: Submit online application with paid invoice and AHRI certificate.

programs.description: Massive suite of rebates for Sacramento residents to eliminate gas from their homes.
programs.application_process: 1. Choose SMUD-authorized contractor. 2. Rebate applied to invoice or submitted online.

programs.description: Targeted incentives for the 9-county SF Bay Area, focusing on the building envelope and HPWH.
programs.application_process: Contractor submits rebate through the BayREN Home+ portal.

programs.description: Performance-based incentives for Southern California residents (Non-LA City) based on actual energy saved.
programs.application_process: Enrollment via project pathway with participating energy rater.

programs.program_name: SCE Charge Ready Home - Panel Rebate
programs.description: Rebates specifically for electrical panel upgrades required to install EV chargers or heat pumps.
programs.application_process: Online application with proof of permit and contractor invoice.

programs.description: Direct rebates for Alameda County residents to support the transition to high-efficiency electric water heating and induction cooking.
programs.application_process: Post-install online application with paid invoice and proof of old gas appliance.

programs.description: Aggressive rebates for San Mateo County residents, including the highest panel upgrade incentives in the state.
programs.application_process: Pre-approval required for HP HVAC. Others are post-install.

programs.description: Incentives for 13 Santa Clara County cities to switch to heat pumps and upgrade electrical panels.
programs.application_process: 1. Pre-Approval MUST happen before installation. 2. Install. 3. Submit claim.

programs.program_name: CleanPowerSF Heat Pump Water Heater Incentive
programs.description: Combines a direct rebate with a multi-year bill credit to offset the electricity costs of a new HPWH.
programs.application_process: Submit rebate claim online; bill credits auto-apply once rebate is approved.

programs.description: Broad program covering 5 counties on the Central Coast for all major electrification measures.
programs.application_process: Online post-install application. Requires photo of installed equipment.

programs.description: Incentives for the North Bay and East Bay, including unique multi-measure bonuses.
programs.application_process: Contractor-submitted for HPWH; consumer-submitted for EV.

programs.description: Additional local rebates for LA and Ventura County residents to install battery storage, stacking with statewide SGIP.
programs.application_process: Online application post-install; must provide proof of CPA enrollment and SGIP status.

programs.description: Incentives for Sonoma and Mendocino residents for smart electrification equipment including heat pump water heaters and smart panels.
programs.application_process: Purchase via SCP online storefront or register existing smart device for monthly bill credits.

programs.description: Program for Yolo County residents to navigate and stack electrification rebates with income-qualified bonuses.
programs.application_process: Enroll for navigation support; rebates are processed through the navigator post-install.

programs.description: Significant local battery storage rebate for San Diego region residents to improve grid resiliency and stack with SGIP.
programs.application_process: Post-install online application; requires interconnection agreement from SDG&E.

programs.description: Rebates for Level 2 EV charging equipment for homes and multi-unit dwellings in MCE's territory.
programs.application_process: Online application with proof of purchase and installation photos.

programs.description: 0% interest financing for energy efficiency retrofits, repaid directly through the monthly PG&E utility bill.

requirements.bill_neutrality: Payment must be less than projected savings

programs.application_process: 1. Energy audit. 2. Application submission. 3. PG&E approval. 4. Installation.

programs.description: Federal tax credit for installing EV charging equipment at a primary residence in qualifying census tracts.

requirements.geographic_restriction: Must be in non-urban or low-income tract

programs.application_process: Claimed annually via federal tax return (Form 8911).

programs.program_name: Federal §25C Energy Efficient Home Improvement Credit
programs.description: EXPIRED FOR 2026 INSTALLS. Provided 30% credit for heat pumps up to $2,000. Included for 2025 tax filing accuracy.
programs.application_process: Claimed via Form 5695 on 2025 tax returns.

programs.description: Financing for energy upgrades repaid through an assessment on the property tax bill. No credit score requirement.
programs.application_process: 1. Property eligibility check. 2. Contractor quote. 3. Funding at closing.

programs.description: Targeted direct installation of low-flow fixtures and HPWH settings for high-usage households in drought-affected zones.
programs.application_process: Selection via PG&E usage data; limited self-enrollment via ESA portal.
cannot_stack_with: TECH (If same equipment is installed free)

programs.description: Electrification navigator and rebate add-ons for residents of Riverside and San Bernardino counties, focusing on closing the cost gap for LMI households.
programs.application_process: 1. Contact Navigator. 2. Site assessment. 3. Contractor install. 4. Post-install rebate payout.

programs.description: Program specifically designed for the unique challenges of rural homeowners in 28 Northern/Central CA counties, including high panel upgrade costs.
programs.application_process: Direct referral via local Community Action Agency or online portal enrollment.

programs.description: High-value vouchers to replace unhealthy wood-burning stoves or fireplaces with zero-emission electric heat pumps.
programs.application_process: 1. Apply for voucher. 2. Receive approval. 3. Contractor installs and destroys old stove. 4. AQMD pays contractor directly.

programs.description: Premium municipal rebates for Palo Alto residents to eliminate gas, including $3,500 for water heaters.
programs.application_process: Online submission of permit, paid invoice, and photos of new equipment.

programs.description: City of Santa Clara municipal utility rebates for appliances and panel upgrades.
programs.application_process: Post-install online application; must include AHRI certificate.

programs.description: Incentives for HVAC, HPWH, and EVs for the City of Roseville.
programs.application_process: Online portal submission of invoice and proof of old unit decommissioning.

programs.description: Targeted electrification support for residents of Riverside and San Bernardino counties. Combines technical Navigator audits with specific rebate adders to eliminate out-of-pocket costs for LMI households.
programs.application_process: 1. Contact I-REN Navigator. 2. Virtual or in-home assessment. 3. Contractor bid review. 4. Rebate reservation and post-install payout.

programs.description: Program serving 28 rural counties in Northern California. Specifically addresses high electrical panel upgrade costs ($5,000) which are a primary barrier in older rural housing stock.
programs.application_process: Referral via local Community Action Agency (CAA) or direct portal enrollment for panel-first electrification.

programs.description: A Performance-Plus incentive for the Central Coast. Links residential heat pump installation with locally trained workforce requirements to provide a bonus rebate for residents.
programs.application_process: Claims submitted via participating contractor portal following the TECH Clean California workflow.

programs.description: A comprehensive direct-benefit program for low-income Anaheim residents. Covers the full cost of specific electrification upgrades or provides significant rebates for high-efficiency heat pumps.
programs.application_process: 1. Apply for eligibility. 2. Pre-inspection. 3. Contractor install. 4. Post-inspection and payment.

programs.description: City-funded rebates for residents switching to electric heat pumps and panel upgrades. Unique for doubling the standard rebate amount for low-income households.
programs.application_process: Post-installation online application via City of Piedmont building portal.

programs.description: Direct rebates for Alameda residents for heat pump water heaters and mini-split HVAC systems. Includes Project EASE subsidies for additional electrification assistance.
programs.application_process: Online submission of contractor invoice and AHRI certificate.

programs.program_name: Colton Electric Utility Residential Heat Pump Rebate
programs.description: Rebates for City of Colton residents to replace old fossil-fuel systems with electric heat pumps. Complemented by specific bill assistance for newly electrified LMI households.
programs.application_process: Application via mail or in-person at Colton City Hall utility desk.

programs.description: High-value grants for residents of Monterey, Santa Cruz, and San Benito counties to replace old wood-burning heating devices with zero-emission electric heat pump systems.
programs.application_process: 1. Apply for voucher. 2. Receive MBARD approval. 3. Contractor install. 4. Destruction of old unit at certified scrap yard. 5. Payout.

programs.program_name: San Joaquin Valley Fireplace & Woodstove Change-Out Program
programs.description: Incentives for residents in the 8-county San Joaquin Valley air basin to replace wood-burning devices. Focuses on reducing particulate matter by switching to electric heat pumps.
programs.application_process: 1. Pre-apply for voucher. 2. Buy and install. 3. Submit proof of destruction of old unit.

programs.program_name: BAAQMD Clean HEET (Home Energy Efficiency Transformation)
programs.description: Grants for Bay Area residents to replace wood-burning appliances with electric heat pumps. Specifically targets Overburdened Communities for maximum funding.
programs.application_process: Online portal application with mandatory photos of existing wood-burning unit.

programs.description: A highly localized program for the Greater Portola Area (Plumas County) aimed at meeting federal air quality standards through 100% electric heating conversion.
programs.application_process: 1. Application submission to NSAQMD. 2. Site visit. 3. Contractor installation. 4. Payout to contractor.

programs.program_name: Berkeley Climate Equity Fund - Resilient Retrofit Grant
programs.description: Pilot fund established by Berkeley City Council to provide deep-decarbonization grants to low-income residents. Covers holistic home electrification including structural resilience, panel upgrades, and heat pump HVAC.
programs.application_process: 1. Pre-screening via Berkeley Climate Equity Collaborative. 2. Site assessment. 3. Contractor selection from preferred list. 4. Direct grant payment to contractor.

programs.description: A Virtual Power Plant (VPP) initiative for Richmond residents. Provides direct-install solar + battery storage + smart heat pump controls at little to no cost for households in environmental justice zones.
programs.application_process: Application via MCE Clean Energy portal; project includes revitalize housing stock efforts and no-cost equipment installs.

programs.description: Funded by the Urban Sustainability Directors Network (USDN), this program provides intragovernmental resilience grants specifically for LMI homeowners in Oakland to perform holistic electrification.
programs.application_process: Verification via the Oakland Building Department's electrification incentive portal.

programs.description: A dedicated city fund that doubles the standard $1,500 rebate for residents under 80% AMI, specifically for heat pump HVAC systems to meet city-wide decarbonization goals.
programs.application_process: Post-installation submission of proof of income and final building permit to city planning department.

programs.description: Launched in early 2026, SDREN provides specialized electrification pathways for San Diego region residents, filling gaps in SDG&E's standard portfolio with a focus on holistic heat pump adoption and panel upgrades.
programs.application_process: 1. Online enrollment. 2. Technical consultation (optional). 3. Contractor install. 4. Post-install rebate claim.

programs.program_name: GRID Alternatives - Tribal Electrification & Solar Program
programs.description: No-cost electrification and solar installations specifically for California Tribal lands. Includes heat pump water heaters and HVAC systems as part of holistic Energy Sovereignty packages.
programs.application_process: 1. Contact GRID Tribal Program Manager. 2. Verification of tribal status and site. 3. Full design and no-cost installation.

programs.description: State-funded program for farmworker households. Provides no-cost energy efficiency, rooftop solar, and heat pump HVAC/water heater upgrades to reduce energy burden.
programs.application_process: Intake via local Community Action Agency (CAA) or LIWP regional administrator.

programs.program_name: SunWork Heat Pump Water Heater LMI Grant
programs.description: SunWork, a 501(c)(3) non-profit, utilizes volunteer labor and dedicated grants to install heat pump water heaters for low-income residents at a fraction of commercial costs.
programs.application_process: 1. Cost estimator screening. 2. Site audit. 3. Volunteer-led installation (licensed supervised).

programs.program_name: Self-Generation Incentive Program (SGIP) - Heat Pump Water Heater
programs.description: SGIP provides significant rebates for heat pump water heaters that function as thermal energy storage. Targeted primarily at low-income and DAC residential customers.
programs.application_process: 1. Online reservation. 2. Proof of install and AHRI certificate. 3. Payout to customer or contractor.
cannot_stack_with: TECH HPWH (In some cases - verify by PA)

programs.program_name: USDA Section 504 Home Repair Loan & Grant
programs.description: Federal funding for rural California homeowners. Provides grants to seniors (62+) and low-interest loans to LMI residents to repair, modernize, or remove health/safety hazards—specifically including the installation of heat pump HVAC systems.
programs.application_process: Contact local USDA Rural Development office. Requires income verification and property eligibility check.

programs.description: Prescriptive rebates for City of Redding residents to replace natural gas or propane systems with high-efficiency electric heat pumps (HVAC) and heat pump water heaters.
programs.application_process: Submit AHRI certificate and final contractor invoice via REU rebate portal.

programs.program_name: Sonoma Clean Power - Lead the Way Electrification
programs.description: High-value incentives for Sonoma and Mendocino County residents. Combines technical support from the SCP Advanced Energy Center with specific point-of-sale discounts for heat pump appliances.
programs.application_process: Point-of-sale discount applied by participating AEC contractors or post-install online claim.

programs.program_name: Silicon Valley Power (SVP) Residential Heat Pump HVAC
programs.description: Targeted HVAC rebates for residents of the City of Santa Clara. Program has specific cycles (Jan/July) and is designed to move customers away from central gas furnaces.
programs.application_process: Online submission with building permit and AHRI certificate.

programs.program_name: Valley Water Residential HPWH Supplemental Rebate
programs.description: A Water-Energy Nexus rebate. Valley Water provides a supplemental $1,000 for heat pump water heaters in Santa Clara County because of their superior water-use efficiency and leakage detection features.
programs.application_process: Verification via the BayREN application portal (automatic adder for SC County residents).

programs.program_name: Lodi Electric Residential Heat Pump Incentive
programs.description: Rebates for Lodi residential customers to upgrade to high-efficiency electric heat pumps and heat pump water heaters, specifically for customers replacing old gas units.
programs.application_process: Online submission of AHRI certificate and final itemized contractor invoice.

programs.program_name: RPU Residential Heat Pump HVAC Rebate
programs.description: Rebates for City of Riverside residents to replace existing HVAC systems with high-efficiency heat pump units. RPU also offers a separate $1,000 rebate for heat pump water heaters.
programs.application_process: Post-installation application with proof of efficiency rating and proof of old unit decommissioning.

programs.program_name: PWP Residential Electrification & Heat Pump Rebate
programs.description: Targeted incentives for Pasadena residents to switch from gas to electric appliances, including significant rebates for heat pump HVAC systems and panel upgrades ($1,500).
programs.application_process: Claims submitted through the PWP online rebate center within 180 days of purchase.

programs.program_name: GWP Smart Home Rebate (Heat Pump Category)
programs.description: GWP provides rebates for high-efficiency electric home systems, including specific line items for heat pump HVAC and heat pump water heaters.
programs.application_process: Online submission with proof of purchase and installation details.

programs.description: One of the most aggressive Muni programs in the state. Provides high-value rebates for heat pump water heaters and HVAC systems, with optional project management support.
programs.application_process: Online claim following permit approval and final inspection by city.

programs.description: A revamped 2026 CCA program for the Central Coast. Provides cash rebates for residents replacing gas appliances with electric heat pumps, including extra funding for LMI customers and those in high-fire zones.
programs.application_process: Reservation via 3CE portal followed by contractor invoice submission.

programs.description: Rebates for Modesto residents to install high-efficiency heat pump systems. MID recently updated their rebate amounts to reflect the higher cost of SEER2 compliant equipment.
programs.application_process: Online submission of AHRI certificate and proof of purchase within 60 days of install.

programs.program_name: TID Residential Heat Pump HVAC Rebate
programs.description: Rebates for Turlock residents for residential heat pump systems, including specific multipliers for those replacing older inefficient resistance heating systems.
programs.application_process: Mail-in or online application with contractor invoice.

programs.program_name: TDPUD Residential Heat Pump HVAC Rebate
programs.description: Specialized high-altitude heat pump incentives for the Truckee region. Includes specific performance requirements for cold-climate heat pumps (CCHP).
programs.application_process: Verification of CCHP listing followed by online claim submission.

programs.program_name: IID Residential Energy Efficiency (Heat Pump Category)
programs.description: Rebates for IID residential customers for heat pump water heaters, intended to offset the higher cost of high-efficiency systems in the desert region.
programs.application_process: Claims submitted within 90 days of purchase via the IID customer portal.

programs.description: Burbank's primary decarbonization fund. Provides tiered rebates for residents to swap gas furnaces and water heaters for electric heat pump technology.
programs.application_process: Online submission with proof of old unit removal and AHRI certificate.

programs.description: Specialized tiered rebates for Healdsburg residents, specifically designed to support the city's 2026 Energy Reach Code requirements for high-efficiency heat pumps.
programs.application_process: Verification via the BayREN application portal or direct city submission.

programs.program_name: Ukiah Residential Energy Efficiency (Heat Pump Category)
programs.description: Ukiah provides comprehensive rebates for various home upgrades, with specific high-value incentives for heat pump HVAC systems.
programs.application_process: Submit claim to Ukiah Electric Utility department with contractor invoice.

programs.program_name: Azusa Light & Water Home Energy Upgrade Program
programs.description: A program specifically for Azusa residents that provides rebates for high-efficiency HVAC and heat pump water heaters.
programs.application_process: Submit proof of purchase and AHRI certificate via the ALW online portal.

programs.description: Incentives for Davis and Woodland residents to switch to all-electric homes. Works in conjunction with regional Switch Is On funding.
programs.application_process: Claim submission via the VCE or Switch Is On incentive portal.

programs.program_name: Pioneer Community Energy - High-Efficiency HVAC Rebate
programs.description: A newly launched 2026 rebate program for residents in Placer and El Dorado Counties. Targeted specifically at heat pump HVAC upgrades.
programs.application_process: Online claim through the Pioneer Energy portal within 60 days of installation.

programs.description: Merced residents can receive rebates for installing heat pump HVAC systems as part of MeID's new residential building electrification pilot.
programs.application_process: Verification via the Switch Is On portal or direct submission to MeID.

programs.program_name: CEA Heat Pump Water Heater Rebate
programs.description: Direct rebates for residents of Carlsbad, Del Mar, Escondido, Oceanside, San Marcos, Solana Beach, and Vista for HPWH installs.
programs.application_process: Online claim within 90 days of install through the CEA program portal.

programs.description: Direct battery storage rebates that can be paired with heat pump systems to create "Virtual Power Plant" ready homes in the San Diego region.
programs.application_process: Application via SDCP portal during open reservation windows.

programs.program_name: City of Shasta Lake Energy Efficiency Rebate
programs.description: Detailed rebates for Shasta Lake residents for high-efficiency electric home upgrades, including heat pump HVAC systems.
programs.application_process: Direct claim to City of Shasta Lake electric utility department.

programs.program_name: Roseville Electric Residential Heat Pump Incentive
programs.description: Distinct from Redding, Roseville offers significant rebates for central heat pumps and mini-splits, with a separate $400 bonus for heat pump dryers.
programs.application_process: Online submission via the Roseville Electric rebate portal.

programs.description: Member-owned cooperative incentives for heat pump HVAC systems in the Sierra Nevada and Plumas County regions.
programs.application_process: Submit rebate form and proof of purchase to the PSREC main office.

programs.description: Rebates for Gridley residents for high-efficiency electric appliances, including heat pump water heaters and HVAC systems.
programs.application_process: Contact City of Gridley electric department for rebate forms.

programs.description: Small-town municipal rebates for Biggs residents upgrading to high-efficiency electric heat pump units.
programs.application_process: Administered via the Northern California Power Agency (NCPA) portal.

programs.description: Incentives for Banning residents to swap gas furnaces for electric heat pumps, helping to offset the cost of new high-efficiency units.
programs.application_process: Submit invoice and proof of purchase to Banning City Hall utility office.

programs.description: Direct cash rebate for residential customers swapping fossil-fuel HVAC for electric heat pumps.
programs.application_process: Purchase equipment; install; submit invoice and proof of gas decommissioning.

programs.description: Specific incentive to drive electrification in the Imperial Valley and Eastern Riverside. Rebate calculated at $400 per ton of cooling capacity.

requirements.note: $400/ton rebate; must replace central gas furnace

programs.application_process: Pre-verify IID account; install unit; submit AHRI certificate and IID application.

programs.program_name: Lodi Residential Heat Pump HVAC Rebate
programs.description: Tiered efficiency rebate for City of Lodi residents moving to high-performance heating/cooling.
programs.application_process: Select SEER2 16+ unit; install; submit City of Lodi rebate form within 90 days.

programs.description: Maintenance and install-level incentive for Moreno Valley residential customers. $75 per unit, limit 2 units.
programs.application_process: Contractor installation; submit MVU form and contractor invoice.

programs.program_name: Trinity PUD Residential Heat Pump Fund
programs.description: Supports cold-climate electrification for remote Northern California residents in Trinity County.
programs.application_process: Submit pre-approval request; install; utility site inspection required.

programs.description: High-value incentive for removing gas infrastructure and installing electric HVAC in Turlock. Requires proof of gas line capping/removal.
programs.application_process: Purchase; install; submit proof of gas-to-electric conversion.

programs.description: Bundled incentive for Modesto Irrigation District customers installing a heat pump alongside a smart thermostat. Cannot be combined with individual unit rebates.

requirements.equipment: Heat Pump HVAC + EnergyStar Smart Thermostat

programs.application_process: Install qualifying HP; register smart thermostat; submit combined rebate form.

programs.program_name: LMUD Air Source Heat Pump Incentive
programs.description: Designed for high-altitude heating needs in the Susanville region of Lassen County.
programs.application_process: Verify equipment meets Lassen climate specs; install; submit to LMUD office.

programs.description: Specific support for rural Anza Electric Cooperative members moving away from propane. Gas-to-electric conversions only.
programs.application_process: Pre-consult with AEC; install; rebate applied to member account.

programs.description: Incentives for dual-fuel and full electric heat pumps in Big Bear mountain communities. Application must be submitted within 60 days of installation.
programs.application_process: Purchase; install; submit application within 60 days.

programs.description: High-altitude, cold-climate focused program for the Truckee/Tahoe region. Contractor must use TDPUD checklist and site verification by PUD is required.

requirements.equipment: ccASHP (Cold Climate Air Source Heat Pumps)
requirements.process: TDPUD contractor checklist required; site verification by PUD

programs.application_process: Contractor must use TDPUD checklist; install; site verification by PUD.

programs.description: 100% cost coverage for total home electrification in the Belle Haven designated equity zone. Designed as 'Total Project Funding' absorbing all other rebates. City manages contractor installation.

requirements.equipment: HP HVAC, HPWH, Panel Upgrades, Appliances

programs.application_process: Neighborhood canvassing/outreach; application; City manages contractor installation.
cannot_stack_with: All other rebates (designed to absorb them)

programs.program_name: San Carlos Peninsula Clean Energy Match
programs.description: City of San Carlos adds a 50% supplemental match to Peninsula Clean Energy (PCE) residential rebates. Mandatory stacking with PCE rebates — must have an approved PCE rebate first.

requirements.prerequisite: Must have approved PCE rebate first

programs.application_process: Receive PCE Rebate; submit PCE approval to San Carlos Building Department.

programs.description: Supplemental local rebate to offset high installation costs of heat pumps in Piedmont. Triggered after building permit issuance and successful inspection.
programs.application_process: Building permit issuance; successful inspection; rebate request.

programs.description: City-funded direct rebate for gas-to-electric heat pump conversions. Apply online to receive a reservation before installation.
programs.application_process: Apply online; receive reservation; install and submit final invoices.

programs.description: High-value grant to swap wood-burning heaters for high-efficiency heat pumps. Seasonal program (Oct-Apr). Currently out of funds — waitlist for 2026.

requirements.process: Pre-qualification; approved installer; stove scrapping required

programs.application_process: Pre-qualification; select approved installer; install HP; scrapping of stove.

programs.description: Targeted electrification support for Modoc County cooperative members of Surprise Valley Electrification Corp. Rebate credited directly to electric bill.
programs.application_process: Inquire via member services; install; rebate credit to electric bill.

programs.description: AQMD grant focused on replacing old wood stoves with electric heat pumps to improve local air quality. Requires destruction of old stove.

requirements.process: Inspection of existing stove; installation of HP; destruction of old stove

programs.application_process: Inspection of existing stove; installation of HP; destruction of old stove.

programs.description: Significant grant for residents in the Lake Tahoe/Sierra region moving to electric heat pumps. Annual fiscal cycle funding.

requirements.process: Apply for voucher; hire contractor; inspection and payment

programs.application_process: Apply for voucher; hire contractor; inspection and payment.

programs.description: Seasonal AQMD grant targeting wood-to-electric conversion in smoke-impacted areas of Paradise and Chico. Requires scrapping of old wood heater.

requirements.process: Pre-qualification; install HP; scrap old heater

programs.application_process: Pre-qualification; install electric HP; scrapping of old wood heater.

programs.description: High-incentive grant for Sutter and Yuba county residents administered by Feather River AQMD. Application must be submitted before removal of old heater.

requirements.process: Application required before removal of old heater

programs.application_process: Application required before removal of old heater; seasonal availability.

programs.description: Rural smoke reduction fund for Tehama County residents administered by Tehama County Air Pollution Control District.
programs.application_process: Apply; pre-inspection; voucher issued.

programs.description: Aggressive municipal adder to phase out gas in Palo Alto. Automatic addition if using a CPAU-certified installer. Does NOT stack with PG&E (Palo Alto is a POU).
programs.application_process: Automatic addition if using a CPAU-certified installer.

programs.description: Direct utility rebate for City of Alameda residents served by Alameda Municipal Power. Tiered rebate $1,500-$2,500 depending on equipment.
programs.application_process: Submit online application with paid invoice.

programs.description: Incentives for high-efficiency cooling/heating in the extreme heat of the Imperial Valley. Tiered rebate $1,200-$2,000 based on high SEER2 rating.
programs.application_process: Submit AHRI certificate and proof of purchase.
